section1:
  body: >
    ## Devcon is the Ethereum conference for developers, thinkers, and makers.


    **Devcon's goal is to push the boundaries of the possible in our mission to
    bring decentralized protocols, tools, and culture to the world.**


    * **Devcon ->**

    * -> is for the builders.

    * -> is not just for developers, it's for the creators, thinkers, and makers
    who wish to improve this world through decentralization.

    * -> is a platform to speak and discuss the topics you are passionate about.

    * -> is sponsor- and shill-free, focusing on what truly matters.

    * -> creates an environment to empower ourselves, and to learn skills
    relevant to using Ethereum.

    * -> brings together innovative minds with the vision to build the new
    internet with Ethereum.
section2:
  top: >
    ## **The Road to Devcon Southeast Asia**


    ### The Road to Devcon is a series of Ethereum events and educational
    initiatives leading up to Devcon, organized by the local communities in
    Southeast Asia.


    **Why bring Devcon to SEA?**


    Ethereum communities in SEA are very active. Many want to see Ethereum
    succeed, because Ethereum has real use cases in SEA, with high crypto
    adoption in Vietnam, the Philippines, Indonesia, and Thailand.


    <Buttons
      Button={[
        { text: "Join the Road to Devcon →", url: "/road-to-devcon/" }
      ]}
    />

  body: >

section4:
  body: >
    ## **Devcon VI Bogotá**


    ### Devcon started as a small meetup of early Ethereum developers in Berlin.
    Today, it has become a family reunion for the global Ethereum community!


    Devcon VI was held in Bogotá, Colombia, with a spirit resonating across
    South and Latin America.


    <Buttons
      Button={[
        {
          text: "Devcon VI Recap →",
          url: "https://blog.ethereum.org/en/2022/11/17/devcon-vi-wrap"
        }
      ]}
    />
section5:
  body: >
    Devcon is geared toward Ethereum's builders, creators, and thinkers who wish
    to improve this world. Programming at Devcon takes a holistic approach and
    aims to engage all attendees through talks, panels, workshops, lightning
    talks, and freeform learning sessions.
